<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-08-17T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-08-17T10:00:00-05:00" n="777" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d777">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711F.1914/8–1747: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Panama</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hines</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Panamá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-08-17T10:00:00-05:00">August 17,
                                    1947—10 a.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>457. <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 337, August 16. Embassy
                            favors presenting to Panama draft G with recommended modifications. This
                            would avoid number of auxiliary notes.</p>
                        <p>Should Panama strongly oppose, we should then present Department’s
                            revision of Alfaro proposal on “take it or leave it” basis.</p>
                        <p>Embassy believes issue if handled as indicated can be concluded by
                            September.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hines</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>